import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    colors = ['red', 'green', 'blue', 'orange']
    markers = ['o', 's', 'v', '^']
    for i, series in enumerate(data['Series'].unique()):
        series_data = data[data['Series'] == series]
        ax.scatter(series_data['X'], series_data['Y'], color=colors[i], marker=markers[i], label=series)
    ax.legend()
    ax.set_xlabel('X')
    ax.set_ylabel('Y')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between X and Y in each series?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    series = data.groupby('Series')
    x_mean = series['X'].mean()
    y_mean = series['Y'].mean()
    x_std = series['X'].std()
    y_std = series['Y'].std()
    ind = np.arange(len(series))
    width = 0.35
    ax.bar(ind - width/2, x_mean, width, yerr=x_std, label='X')
    ax.bar(ind + width/2, y_mean, width, yerr=y_std, label='Y')
    ax.set_xticks(ind)
    ax.set_xticklabels(series.groups.keys())
    ax.set_xlabel('Series')
    ax.set_ylabel('Value')
    ax.set_title('What is the mean and standard deviation of X and Y for each series?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='X', hue='Series', ax=axs[0], kde=True, stat='density', common_norm=False, palette='Set1')
    axs[0].set_title('Distribution of X across all series')
    axs[0].axvline(data['X'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    axs[0].axvline(data['X'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    axs[0].legend()

    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Y', hue='Series', ax=axs[1], kde=True, stat='density', common_norm=False, palette='Set1')
    axs[1].set_title('Distribution of Y across all series')
    axs[1].axvline(data['Y'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    axs[1].axvline(data['Y'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    axs[1].legend()

    plt.suptitle('What is the distribution of X and Y across all series?')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="ticks")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x="X", y="Y", hue="Series", data=data, ax=ax)
    corr = data.groupby('Series').corr().iloc[0::2,-1].values
    corr = [f'{c:.2f}' for c in corr]
    corr = ', '.join(corr)
    ax.text(0.05, 0.95, f'Correlation: {corr}', transform=ax.transAxes, fontsize=12, verticalalignment='top')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between X and Y across all series?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x="Series", y="X-Y", data=data, palette="Set3", ax=ax)
    plt.axhline(y=0, color='r', linestyle='--', label='0')
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title('What is the difference between the means of X and Y in each series?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Series')
    plt.ylabel('X-Y')
    return plt

data['X-Y'] = data['X'] - data['Y']
chart = plot(data)
